en-US: FWS, a vibrant webserver playground written in Go, offers a hub of APIs, user and realm management, and a wealth of digital functionalities. It adapts uniquely to both client-side and server-side locales through a simple CSV file. Compatible with HTMX and supporting SSR builds with Vite for JavaScript users, its standout feature is the reverse proxy mode, enabling use in preferred languages while leveraging FWS's extensive features, primarily through headers. Continuously evolving, FWS hosts several projects.
